#    - cd training
#    - remove files with the extensions xml, csv  and log
#    - remove all files with the name starteding with "ba" 
#    - make all files executable
#    - remove all content
#    - create a new file named "hello.txt" with the content "Hello World !"
#    - copy all content of "practice/tasks1" to the dir "training"
#    - rename all *.log files to the corresponding *.transcript
#    - print the first 3 lines of each file
#    - print the last 3 lines of each file
#
#    - list the content of "practice/tasks1"  directory with human-readable file size and sorted by last modified 
#    - list the content of "practice/tasks1"  directory with human-readable file size, sorted by last modified, without group nor owner 
#    - list the content of "practice/tasks1"  directory by separating entries by comma and in reverse order 
#    - list the content of "practice/tasks1"  directory in a single column sorted by file extension
#    - list all hidden files in "practice" directory
#    - get the length of longest line in tasks1/ samplesite.html file 
#    - rename all “*.pdf” files under practice/tasks1 to “*.pdf_backup”
#
#    - display a list of all users in a system  registered in /etc/passwd  and their login shell
